HEADWORD: Alnager
<hw>Al"na*ger</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Alnage</er>.]</ety> <def>A measure by the ell; formerly a sworn
officer in England, whose duty was to inspect and measure woolen cloth,
and fix upon it a seal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

